{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Bootstrap Grid Column Display Issues\n\nCorrect the Bootstrap grid layout system where columns are not displaying the expected number of elements per row according to their class definitions.\n\nCurrent Issues:\n- Elements with .col-lg-4 class display only 2 items per row instead of the expected 3 (12/4=3)\n- Elements with .col-md-3 class display only 3 items per row instead of the expected 4 (12/3=4)\n- Issue is visible in the \"Why Us\" section and potentially other sections\n\nRequirements:\n- Audit all sections using Bootstrap grid classes (.col-xs-*, .col-sm-*, .col-md-*, .col-lg-*, .col-xl-*)\n- Identify conflicting CSS rules overriding Bootstrap's default column widths\n- Remove or adjust custom width, padding, or margin rules causing incorrect column calculations\n- Verify correct number of columns display at each breakpoint:\n  - .col-lg-4 should show 3 columns on large screens\n  - .col-md-3 should show 4 columns on medium screens\n  - Validate other column classes follow 12-column grid math\n- Test responsive behavior across all breakpoints (xs, sm, md, lg, xl)\n- Ensure consistent spacing and alignment after fixes\n- Verify no horizontal overflow or layout breaks\n\nSuccess Criteria:\n- All Bootstrap column classes render the mathematically correct number of columns per row\n- No visual regressions in spacing, alignment, or responsive behavior\n- Layout remains consistent across different screen sizes",
